  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Friday. Today was our school's annual sports day, and my body is currently filing several complaints against me.",
      "zh": "星期五。今天是我們學校一年一度的運動會，我的身體現在正對我提出好幾項抗議。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our PE teacher is famously strict, the kind of person who considers \"walking\" during warm-up laps a serious crime.",
      "zh": "我們的體育老師出了名的嚴格，那種把熱身跑步時「用走的」當成重大犯罪的類型。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Effort matters more than natural talent,\" he shouted at the start of the day, apparently as a general life philosophy and not just about sports.",
      "zh": "「努力比天生的才能更重要，」他在一開始就大喊，聽起來與其說是講運動，更像是一句人生哲學。"
    },
    {
      "en": "My first event was badminton doubles with Bernice, who has surprisingly rapid reflexes for someone who claims to hate exercise.",
      "zh": "我的第一個項目是跟 Bernice 搭檔打羽毛球雙打，她的反應速度快得驚人，實在不像一個自稱討厭運動的人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We lost our first match, badly, but our second match ended in a genuine victory, mostly thanks to Bernice's skill at the net.",
      "zh": "我們第一場輸得很慘，但第二場真的贏了，主要要感謝 Bernice 在網前展現的球技。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After badminton, I joined the soccer match, where my main skill turned out to be running away from the ball with great enthusiasm.",
      "zh": "羽球賽後，我加入了足球賽，結果我最擅長的技能，居然是很有幹勁地跑離球。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Our team still managed to score two goals, neither of which I was directly responsible for, but I cheered very loudly for both.",
      "zh": "我們隊還是踢進了兩球，雖然兩球都跟我沒什麼直接關係，但我為兩球都大聲歡呼了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Next was football, which apparently is a completely different sport in some countries, a fact that confused half our class all morning.",
      "zh": "接下來是美式足球，顯然在有些國家這是完全不同的一種運動，這件事讓我們班一整個早上都搞不清楚。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The best runner in our grade finished the relay race so far ahead that the rest of us were basically jogging toward a memory of where he used to be.",
      "zh": "我們年級跑最快的那個人在接力賽中遙遙領先，我們其他人基本上只是朝著他曾經出現的殘影慢跑而已。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's class had their own event: a hopping race where every student had to hop, not run, across the entire field.",
      "zh": "William 那個年級有他們自己的項目：一場跳躍賽跑，每個學生必須從整個操場的這頭一路跳到那頭，不准用跑的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He hopped his way to third place and announced it as though he had personally set a world record for hopping speed.",
      "zh": "他跳著跳著拿到了第三名，宣布這件事的樣子，好像他個人剛創下了跳躍速度的世界紀錄一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Third place with that much pride is basically first place,\" I told him, and he seemed to genuinely agree with that logic.",
      "zh": "「用那種驕傲的態度拿第三名，基本上就等於第一名，」我跟他說，他似乎真心認同這個邏輯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the final event, a long-distance jog around the whole field, I had very little power left in my legs.",
      "zh": "到了最後一項，繞整個操場一圈的長跑，我的腿已經幾乎沒有力氣了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I did not finish first, or even close to first, but I did finish, which our PE teacher said counts as a personal victory.",
      "zh": "我不是第一個抵達，甚至差得很遠，但我確實跑完了，我們體育老師說這也算是一種個人的勝利。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A powerful finish is not always about speed,\" he said. \"Sometimes it is just about not giving up halfway through.\"",
      "zh": "「有力的完賽不一定是靠速度，」他說：「有時候只是關於不在半路上放棄而已。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice and I collapsed onto the grass afterward, too tired to move, silently agreeing that sports day is somehow both fun and a form of punishment.",
      "zh": "事後 Bernice 和我癱倒在草地上，累到動不了，默默地都同意，運動會不知怎麼地同時是好玩的事，也是一種懲罰。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: my badminton skill is real, my soccer skill is questionable, and my pride survived mostly because William's did too.",
      "zh": "今日心得：我的羽球技術是真的不錯，足球技術很可疑，而我的自尊心之所以還撐得住，主要是因為 William 的自尊心也撐住了。"
    }
  ],
